ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO
RUN NORTH AND SOUTH

Front Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.E. corner of Wall Street. The view shows a general view eastward, over the East River to Brooklyn. (Front Street, is arbitrarily set to run north and south from Coenties Slip, to the Brooklyn Bridge).

P. L. Sperr.

Wall Street, west from Front Street, showing mainly the south side of same. Note the South Ferry division of the Second and Third Aves. Elevated Lines on Pearl Street. At the S.W. corner of that point appears the 25-storied triangular structure of the Munson Steamship Line. Obscuring same is the 12-story Orient Building at the S.E. corner of that point.

November 7, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
